HEADWORD: Sublate
<hw>Sub"late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>sublatus</ets>, used as p. p. of <ets>tollere</ets> to take away.
See <er>Tolerate</er>.]</ety> <def>To take or carry away; to
remove.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>E. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

